Package: Tivy
Type: Package
Title: Tools for Fisheries Data Analysis and Visualization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Hans", "Ttito", 
                  email = "kvttitos@gmail.com", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3732-9419"))
Description: Comprehensive toolkit for processing, analyzing, and visualizing fisheries data from Peru's Ministry of Production (PRODUCE). Handles fishing logbooks, length frequency data, vessel tracking, and regulatory announcements including preventive closure notifications. Features include automated data processing from multiple file formats, coordinate conversion and validation, spatial analysis of fishing zones, juvenile fish analysis, and interactive/static visualization tools. Contains built-in datasets of Peruvian coastal coordinates and parallel lines at different nautical mile distances for analyzing fishing activities within regulatory zones. Supports both English and Spanish data formats commonly used in Latin American fisheries management.
URL: https://github.com/yourusername/Tivy
